description:
Hi,

Our Azure Application Gateway (appgw-prod-eus2-01) is returning 502 Bad Gateway
errors intermittently. I exported the current backend pool configuration:

```json
{
  "backendAddressPools": [
    {
      "name": "pool-api-prod",
      "properties": {
        "backendAddresses": [
          { "ipAddress": "10.42.1.10" },
          { "ipAddress": "10.42.1.11" },
          { "ipAddress": "10.42.1.12" },
          { "ipAddress": "10.42.1.13" }
        ],
        "provisioningState": "Succeeded"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "pool-web-prod",
      "properties": {
        "backendAddresses": [
          { "ipAddress": "10.42.2.10" },
          { "ipAddress": "10.42.2.11" },
          { "ipAddress": "10.42.2.12" }
        ],
        "provisioningState": "Succeeded"
      }
    }
  ],
  "backendHttpSettingsCollection": [
    {
      "name": "http-settings-api",
      "properties": {
        "port": 8443,
        "protocol": "Https",
        "requestTimeout": 30,
        "probe": { "id": "/subscriptions/.../probes/probe-api-health" },
        "hostName": "api-internal.contoso.com",
        "pickHostNameFromBackendAddress": false
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "http-settings-web",
      "properties": {
        "port": 443,
        "protocol": "Https",
        "requestTimeout": 60,
        "probe": { "id": "/subscriptions/.../probes/probe-web-health" },
        "hostName": "www-internal.contoso.com",
        "pickHostNameFromBackendAddress": false
      }
    }
  ],
  "probes": [
    {
      "name": "probe-api-health",
      "properties": {
        "protocol": "Https",
        "host": "api-internal.contoso.com",
        "path": "/health",
        "interval": 30,
        "timeout": 10,
        "unhealthyThreshold": 3
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "probe-web-health",
      "properties": {
        "protocol": "Https",
        "host": "www-internal.contoso.com",
        "path": "/healthz",
        "interval": 30,
        "timeout": 10,
        "unhealthyThreshold": 3
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

The 502 errors happen mostly between 09:00-09:30 when traffic spikes. The health
probes seem to be passing fine in Azure Portal. Could be a backend timeout issue
since the API pool timeout is only 30 seconds.

Henrik Svensson
Cloud Infrastructure, New York

